AMRadioChannel.label: AMRadioChannel
AMRadioChannel.comment: A radio channel that uses AM.

APIReference.label: APIReference
APIReference.comment: Reference documentation for application programming interfaces (APIs).

AcceptAction.label: AcceptAction
AcceptAction.comment:
The act of committing to/adopting an object.



Related actions:



  • RejectAction: The antonym of AcceptAction.

Accommodation.label: Accommodation
Accommodation.comment:
An accommodation is a place that can accommodate human beings, e.g. a hotel room, a camping pitch, or a meeting room. Many accommodations are for overnight stays, but this is not a mandatory requirement.For more specific types of accommodations not defined in schema.org, one can use additionalType with external vocabularies.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

AccountingService.label: AccountingService
AccountingService.comment:
Accountancy business.



As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).

AchieveAction.label: AchieveAction
AchieveAction.comment: The act of accomplishing something via previous efforts. It is an instantaneous action rather than an ongoing process.

Action.label: Action
Action.comment:
An action performed by a direct agent and indirect participants upon a direct object. Optionally happens at a location with the help of an inanimate instrument. The execution of the action may produce a result. Specific action sub-type documentation specifies the exact expectation of each argument/role.



See also blog post and Actions overview document.

ActionAccessSpecification.label: ActionAccessSpecification
ActionAccessSpecification.comment: A set of requirements that a must be fulfilled in order to perform an Action.

ActivateAction.label: ActivateAction
ActivateAction.comment: The act of starting or activating a device or application (e.g. starting a timer or turning on a flashlight).

ActiveActionStatus.label: ActiveActionStatus
ActiveActionStatus.comment: An in-progress action (e.g, while watching the movie, or driving to a location).

AddAction.label: AddAction
AddAction.comment: The act of editing by adding an object to a collection.

AdministrativeArea.label: AdministrativeArea
AdministrativeArea.comment: A geographical region, typically under the jurisdiction of a particular government.

AggregateOffer.label: AggregateOffer
AggregateOffer.comment:
When a single product is associated with multiple offers (for example, the same pair of shoes is offered by different merchants), then AggregateOffer can be used.



Note: AggregateOffers are normally expected to associate multiple offers that all share the same defined businessFunction value, or default to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell if businessFunction is not explicitly defined.

AggregateRating.label: AggregateRating
AggregateRating.comment: The average rating based on multiple ratings or reviews.

AgreeAction.label: AgreeAction
AgreeAction.comment: The act of expressing a consistency of opinion with the object. An agent agrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

Airline.label: Airline
Airline.comment: An organization that provides flights for passengers.

AlignmentObject.label: AlignmentObject
AlignmentObject.comment: An intangible item that describes an alignment between a learning resource and a node in an educational framework.

AllWheelDriveConfiguration.label: AllWheelDriveConfiguration
AllWheelDriveConfiguration.comment: All-wheel Drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives all four wheels.

AllocateAction.label: AllocateAction
AllocateAction.comment: The act of organizing tasks/objects/events by associating resources to it.

Answer.label: Answer
Answer.comment: An answer offered to a question; perhaps correct, perhaps opinionated or wrong.

Apartment.label: Apartment
Apartment.comment: An apartment (in American English) or flat (in British English) is a self-contained housing unit (a type of residential real estate) that occupies only part of a building (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apartment).

AppendAction.label: AppendAction
AppendAction.comment: The act of inserting at the end if an ordered collection.

ApplyAction.label: ApplyAction
ApplyAction.comment:
The act of registering to an organization/service without the guarantee to receive it.



Related actions:



  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, ApplyAction has no guarantees that the application will be accepted.

ArriveAction.label: ArriveAction
ArriveAction.comment: The act of arriving at a place. An agent arrives at a destination from a fromLocation, optionally with participants.

Article.label: Article
Article.comment:
An article, such as a news article or piece of investigative report. Newspapers and magazines have articles of many different types and this is intended to cover them all.



See also blog post.

AskAction.label: AskAction
AskAction.comment:
The act of posing a question / favor to someone.



Related actions:



  • ReplyAction: Appears generally as a response to AskAction.

AssessAction.label: AssessAction
AssessAction.comment: The act of forming one's opinion, reaction or sentiment.

AssignAction.label: AssignAction
AssignAction.comment: The act of allocating an action/event/task to some destination (someone or something).

Attorney.label: Attorney
Attorney.comment:
Professional service: Attorney.



This type is deprecated - LegalService is more inclusive and less ambiguous.

Audience.label: Audience
Audience.comment: Intended audience for an item, i.e. the group for whom the item was created.

AudiobookFormat.label: AudiobookFormat
AudiobookFormat.comment: Book format: Audiobook. This is an enumerated value for use with the bookFormat property. There is also a type 'Audiobook' in the bib extension which includes Audiobook specific properties.

AuthorizeAction.label: AuthorizeAction
AuthorizeAction.comment: The act of granting permission to an object.

BankAccount.label: BankAccount
BankAccount.comment: A product or service offered by a bank whereby one may deposit, withdraw or transfer money and in some cases be paid interest.

Barcode.label: Barcode
Barcode.comment: An image of a visual machine-readable code such as a barcode or QR code.

BedAndBreakfast.label: BedAndBreakfast
BedAndBreakfast.comment:
Bed and breakfast.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

BedDetails.label: BedDetails
BedDetails.comment: An entity holding detailed information about the available bed types, e.g. the quantity of twin beds for a hotel room. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you can use bed directly with a text. See also BedType (under development).

BedType.label: BedType
BedType.comment: A type of bed. This is used for indicating the bed or beds available in an accommodation.

BefriendAction.label: BefriendAction
BefriendAction.comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone (object) mutually/bidirectionally/symmetrically.



Related actions:



  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, BefriendAction implies that the connection is reciprocal.

BoardingPolicyType.label: BoardingPolicyType
BoardingPolicyType.comment: A type of boarding policy used by an airline.

BodyOfWater.label: BodyOfWater
BodyOfWater.comment: A body of water, such as a sea, ocean, or lake.

BookFormatType.label: BookFormatType
BookFormatType.comment: The publication format of the book.

BookSeries.label: BookSeries
BookSeries.comment: A series of books. Included books can be indicated with the hasPart property.

BorrowAction.label: BorrowAction
BorrowAction.comment:
The act of obtaining an object under an agreement to return it at a later date. Reciprocal of LendAction.



Related actions:



  • LendAction: Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Brand.label: Brand
Brand.comment: A brand is a name used by an organization or business person for labeling a product, product group, or similar.

BreadcrumbList.label: BreadcrumbList
BreadcrumbList.comment:
A BreadcrumbList is an ItemList consisting of a chain of linked Web pages, typically described using at least their URL and their name, and typically ending with the current page.



The position property is used to reconstruct the order of the items in a BreadcrumbList The convention is that a breadcrumb list has an itemListOrder of ItemListOrderAscending (lower values listed first), and that the first items in this list correspond to the "top" or beginning of the breadcrumb trail, e.g. with a site or section homepage. The specific values of 'position' are not assigned meaning for a BreadcrumbList, but they should be integers, e.g. beginning with '1' for the first item in the list.

BroadcastChannel.label: BroadcastChannel
BroadcastChannel.comment: A unique instance of a BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

BroadcastEvent.label: BroadcastEvent
BroadcastEvent.comment: An over the air or online broadcast event.

BroadcastFrequencySpecification.label: BroadcastFrequencySpecification
BroadcastFrequencySpecification.comment: The frequency in MHz and the modulation used for a particular BroadcastService.

BroadcastService.label: BroadcastService
BroadcastService.comment: A delivery service through which content is provided via broadcast over the air or online.

BusReservation.label: BusReservation
BusReservation.comment:
A reservation for bus travel.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use Offer.

BusTrip.label: BusTrip
BusTrip.comment: A trip on a commercial bus line.

BusinessAudience.label: BusinessAudience
BusinessAudience.comment: A set of characteristics belonging to businesses, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

BusinessEntityType.label: BusinessEntityType
BusinessEntityType.comment:
A business entity type is a conceptual entity representing the legal form, the size, the main line of business, the position in the value chain, or any combination thereof, of an organization or business person.



Commonly used values:



  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Business
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Enduser
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PublicInstitution
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Reseller

BusinessFunction.label: BusinessFunction
BusinessFunction.comment:
The business function specifies the type of activity or access (i.e., the bundle of rights) offered by the organization or business person through the offer. Typical are sell, rental or lease, maintenance or repair, manufacture / produce, recycle / dispose, engineering / construction, or installation. Proprietary specifications of access rights are also instances of this class.



Commonly used values:



  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ConstructionInstallation
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Dispose
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#LeaseOut
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Maintain
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ProvideService
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Repair
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Buy

BuyAction.label: BuyAction
BuyAction.comment: The act of giving money to a seller in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent buys an object, product, or service from a seller for a price. Reciprocal of SellAction.

CableOrSatelliteService.label: CableOrSatelliteService
CableOrSatelliteService.comment: A service which provides access to media programming like TV or radio. Access may be via cable or satellite.

Campground.label: Campground
Campground.comment:
A camping site, campsite, or Campground is a place used for overnight stay in the outdoors, typically containing individual CampingPitch locations.



In British English a campsite is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individual, family, group, or military unit can pitch a tent or park a camper; a campground may contain many campsites (Source: Wikipedia see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campsite).



See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

CampingPitch.label: CampingPitch
CampingPitch.comment:
A CampingPitch is an individual place for overnight stay in the outdoors, typically being part of a larger camping site, or Campground.



In British English a campsite, or campground, is an area, usually divided into a number of pitches, where people can camp overnight using tents or camper vans or caravans; this British English use of the word is synonymous with the American English expression campground. In American English the term campsite generally means an area where an individual, family, group, or military unit can pitch a tent or park a camper; a campground may contain many campsites.(Source: Wikipedia see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Campsite).



See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Canal.label: Canal
Canal.comment: A canal, like the Panama Canal.

CancelAction.label: CancelAction
CancelAction.comment:
The act of asserting that a future event/action is no longer going to happen.



Related actions:



  • ConfirmAction: The antonym of CancelAction.

Car.label: Car
Car.comment: A car is a wheeled, self-powered motor vehicle used for transportation.

CheckAction.label: CheckAction
CheckAction.comment: An agent inspects, determines, investigates, inquires, or examines an object's accuracy, quality, condition, or state.

CheckInAction.label: CheckInAction
CheckInAction.comment:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their arrival by registering/confirming for a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or at a place (e.g. hotel), possibly resulting in a result (boarding pass, etc).



Related actions:



  • CheckOutAction: The antonym of CheckInAction.
  • ArriveAction: Unlike ArriveAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service.
  • ConfirmAction: Unlike ConfirmAction, CheckInAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the start of a previously reserved service rather than its validity/existence.

CheckOutAction.label: CheckOutAction
CheckOutAction.comment:
The act of an agent communicating (service provider, social media, etc) their departure of a previously reserved service (e.g. flight check in) or place (e.g. hotel).



Related actions:



  • CheckInAction: The antonym of CheckOutAction.
  • DepartAction: Unlike DepartAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.
  • CancelAction: Unlike CancelAction, CheckOutAction implies that the agent is informing/confirming the end of a previously reserved service.

ChooseAction.label: ChooseAction
ChooseAction.comment: The act of expressing a preference from a set of options or a large or unbounded set of choices/options.

CivicStructure.label: CivicStructure
CivicStructure.comment: A public structure, such as a town hall or concert hall.

ClaimReview.label: ClaimReview
ClaimReview.comment: A fact-checking review of claims made (or reported) in some creative work (referenced via itemReviewed).

Clip.label: Clip
Clip.comment: A short TV or radio program or a segment/part of a program.

CoOp.label: CoOp
CoOp.comment: Play mode: CoOp. Co-operative games, where you play on the same team with friends.

Code.label: Code
Code.comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

CollegeOrUniversity.label: CollegeOrUniversity
CollegeOrUniversity.comment: A college, university, or other third-level educational institution.

Comment.label: Comment
Comment.comment: A comment on an item - for example, a comment on a blog post. The comment's content is expressed via the text property, and its topic via about, properties shared with all CreativeWorks.

CommentAction.label: CommentAction
CommentAction.comment: The act of generating a comment about a subject.

CommentPermission.label: CommentPermission
CommentPermission.comment: Permission to add comments to the document.

CommunicateAction.label: CommunicateAction
CommunicateAction.comment: The act of conveying information to another person via a communication medium (instrument) such as speech, email, or telephone conversation.

CompletedActionStatus.label: CompletedActionStatus
CompletedActionStatus.comment: An action that has already taken place.

CompoundPriceSpecification.label: CompoundPriceSpecification
CompoundPriceSpecification.comment: A compound price specification is one that bundles multiple prices that all apply in combination for different dimensions of consumption. Use the name property of the attached unit price specification for indicating the dimension of a price component (e.g. "electricity" or "final cleaning").

ComputerLanguage.label: ComputerLanguage
ComputerLanguage.comment: This type covers computer programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, as well as other language-like computer representations. Natural languages are best represented with the Language type.

ConfirmAction.label: ConfirmAction
ConfirmAction.comment:
The act of notifying someone that a future event/action is going to happen as expected.



Related actions:



  • CancelAction: The antonym of ConfirmAction.

ContactPoint.label: ContactPoint
ContactPoint.comment: A contact point—for example, a Customer Complaints department.

ContactPointOption.label: ContactPointOption
ContactPointOption.comment: Enumerated options related to a ContactPoint.

Continent.label: Continent
Continent.comment: One of the continents (for example, Europe or Africa).

ControlAction.label: ControlAction
ControlAction.comment: An agent controls a device or application.

Conversation.label: Conversation
Conversation.comment: One or more messages between organizations or people on a particular topic. Individual messages can be linked to the conversation with isPartOf or hasPart properties.

Course.label: Course
Course.comment: A description of an educational course which may be offered as distinct instances at which take place at different times or take place at different locations, or be offered through different media or modes of study. An educational course is a sequence of one or more educational events and/or creative works which aims to build knowledge, competence or ability of learners.

CourseInstance.label: CourseInstance
CourseInstance.comment: An instance of a Course which is distinct from other instances because it is offered at a different time or location or through different media or modes of study or to a specific section of students.

CreateAction.label: CreateAction
CreateAction.comment: The act of deliberately creating/producing/generating/building a result out of the agent.

CreativeWork.label: CreativeWork
CreativeWork.comment: The most generic kind of creative work, including books, movies, photographs, software programs, etc.

CreativeWorkSeason.label: CreativeWorkSeason
CreativeWorkSeason.comment: A media season e.g. tv, radio, video game etc.

CreativeWorkSeries.label: CreativeWorkSeries
CreativeWorkSeries.comment:
A CreativeWorkSeries in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike ItemList which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as tv, radio and games).



Specific subtypes are available for describing TVSeries, RadioSeries, MovieSeries, BookSeries, Periodical and VideoGameSeries. In each case, the hasPart / isPartOf properties can be used to relate the CreativeWorkSeries to its parts. The general CreativeWorkSeries type serves largely just to organize these more specific and practical subtypes.



It is common for properties applicable to an item from the series to be usefully applied to the containing group. Schema.org attempts to anticipate some of these cases, but publishers should be free to apply properties of the series parts to the series as a whole wherever they seem appropriate.

CreditCard.label: CreditCard
CreditCard.comment:
A card payment method of a particular brand or name. Used to mark up a particular payment method and/or the financial product/service that supplies the card account.



Commonly used values:



  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#AmericanExpress
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DinersClub
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Discover
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#JCB
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#MasterCard
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#VISA

CurrencyConversionService.label: CurrencyConversionService
CurrencyConversionService.comment: A service to convert funds from one currency to another currency.

DamagedCondition.label: DamagedCondition
DamagedCondition.comment: Indicates that the item is damaged.

DanceGroup.label: DanceGroup
DanceGroup.comment: A dance group—for example, the Alvin Ailey Dance Theater or Riverdance.

DataFeed.label: DataFeed
DataFeed.comment: A single feed providing structured information about one or more entities or topics.

DataFeedItem.label: DataFeedItem
DataFeedItem.comment: A single item within a larger data feed.

DataType.label: DataType
DataType.comment: The basic data types such as Integers, Strings, etc.

Dataset.label: Dataset
Dataset.comment: A body of structured information describing some topic(s) of interest.

Date.label: Date
Date.comment: A date value in ISO 8601 date format.

DateTime.label: DateTime
DateTime.comment: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm] (see Chapter 5.4 of ISO 8601).

DatedMoneySpecification.label: DatedMoneySpecification
DatedMoneySpecification.comment: A DatedMoneySpecification represents monetary values with optional start and end dates. For example, this could represent an employee's salary over a specific period of time. Note: This type has been superseded by MonetaryAmount use of that type is recommended

DayOfWeek.label: DayOfWeek
DayOfWeek.comment:
The day of the week, e.g. used to specify to which day the opening hours of an OpeningHoursSpecification refer.



Originally, URLs from GoodRelations were used (for Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday plus a special entry for PublicHolidays); these have now been integrated directly into schema.org.

DeactivateAction.label: DeactivateAction
DeactivateAction.comment: The act of stopping or deactivating a device or application (e.g. stopping a timer or turning off a flashlight).

DefenceEstablishment.label: DefenceEstablishment
DefenceEstablishment.comment: A defence establishment, such as an army or navy base.

DeleteAction.label: DeleteAction
DeleteAction.comment: The act of editing a recipient by removing one of its objects.

DeliveryChargeSpecification.label: DeliveryChargeSpecification
DeliveryChargeSpecification.comment: The price for the delivery of an offer using a particular delivery method.

DeliveryEvent.label: DeliveryEvent
DeliveryEvent.comment: An event involving the delivery of an item.

DeliveryMethod.label: DeliveryMethod
DeliveryMethod.comment:
A delivery method is a standardized procedure for transferring the product or service to the destination of fulfillment chosen by the customer. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the organization or group that is the contracting party for the sending organization or person.



Commonly used values:



  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeDirectDownload
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeFreight
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeMail
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModeOwnFleet
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DeliveryModePickUp
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

Demand.label: Demand
Demand.comment: A demand entity represents the public, not necessarily binding, not necessarily exclusive, announcement by an organization or person to seek a certain type of goods or services. For describing demand using this type, the very same properties used for Offer apply.

DepartAction.label: DepartAction
DepartAction.comment: The act of  departing from a place. An agent departs from an fromLocation for a destination, optionally with participants.

DepositAccount.label: DepositAccount
DepositAccount.comment: A type of Bank Account with a main purpose of depositing funds to gain interest or other benefits.

DiabeticDiet.label: DiabeticDiet
DiabeticDiet.comment: A diet appropriate for people with diabetes.

DigitalDocumentPermission.label: DigitalDocumentPermission
DigitalDocumentPermission.comment: A permission for a particular person or group to access a particular file.

DigitalDocumentPermissionType.label: DigitalDocumentPermissionType
DigitalDocumentPermissionType.comment: A type of permission which can be granted for accessing a digital document.

DisagreeAction.label: DisagreeAction
DisagreeAction.comment: The act of expressing a difference of opinion with the object. An agent disagrees to/about an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

Discontinued.label: Discontinued
Discontinued.comment: Indicates that the item has been discontinued.

DiscoverAction.label: DiscoverAction
DiscoverAction.comment: The act of discovering/finding an object.

DiscussionForumPosting.label: DiscussionForumPosting
DiscussionForumPosting.comment: A posting to a discussion forum.

DislikeAction.label: DislikeAction
DislikeAction.comment: The act of expressing a negative sentiment about the object. An agent dislikes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

Distance.label: Distance
Distance.comment: Properties that take Distances as values are of the form '<Number> <Length unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 ft'.

DonateAction.label: DonateAction
DonateAction.comment: The act of providing goods, services, or money without compensation, often for philanthropic reasons.

DownloadAction.label: DownloadAction
DownloadAction.comment: The act of downloading an object.

DrawAction.label: DrawAction
DrawAction.comment: The act of producing a visual/graphical representation of an object, typically with a pen/pencil and paper as instruments.

DriveWheelConfigurationValue.label: DriveWheelConfigurationValue
DriveWheelConfigurationValue.comment: A value indicating which roadwheels will receive torque.

EatAction.label: EatAction
EatAction.comment: The act of swallowing solid objects.

EmergencyService.label: EmergencyService
EmergencyService.comment: An emergency service, such as a fire station or ER.

EmployeeRole.label: EmployeeRole
EmployeeRole.comment: A subclass of OrganizationRole used to describe employee relationships.

EmployerAggregateRating.label: EmployerAggregateRating
EmployerAggregateRating.comment: An aggregate rating of an Organization related to its role as an employer.

EndorsementRating.label: EndorsementRating
EndorsementRating.comment:
An EndorsementRating is a rating that expresses some level of endorsement, for example inclusion in a "critic's pick" blog, a"Like" or "+1" on a social network. It can be considered the result of an EndorseAction in which the object of the action is rated positively bysome agent. As is common elsewhere in schema.org, it is sometimes more useful to describe the results of such an action without explicitly describing the Action.



An EndorsementRating may be part of a numeric scale or organized system, but this is not required: having an explicit type for indicating a positive,endorsement rating is particularly useful in the absence of numeric scales as it helps consumers understand that the rating is broadly positive.

Energy.label: Energy
Energy.comment: Properties that take Energy as values are of the form '<Number> <Energy unit of measure>'.

EngineSpecification.label: EngineSpecification
EngineSpecification.comment: Information about the engine of the vehicle. A vehicle can have multiple engines represented by multiple engine specification entities.

EntryPoint.label: EntryPoint
EntryPoint.comment: An entry point, within some Web-based protocol.

Enumeration.label: Enumeration
Enumeration.comment: Lists or enumerations—for example, a list of cuisines or music genres, etc.

Episode.label: Episode
Episode.comment: A media episode (e.g. TV, radio, video game) which can be part of a series or season.

Event.label: Event
Event.comment: An event happening at a certain time and location, such as a concert, lecture, or festival. Ticketing information may be added via the offers property. Repeated events may be structured as separate Event objects.

EventCancelled.label: EventCancelled
EventCancelled.comment: The event has been cancelled. If the event has multiple startDate values, all are assumed to be cancelled. Either startDate or previousStartDate may be used to specify the event's cancelled date(s).

EventPostponed.label: EventPostponed
EventPostponed.comment: The event has been postponed and no new date has been set. The event's previousStartDate should be set.

EventRescheduled.label: EventRescheduled
EventRescheduled.comment: The event has been rescheduled. The event's previousStartDate should be set to the old date and the startDate should be set to the event's new date. (If the event has been rescheduled multiple times, the previousStartDate property may be repeated).

EventReservation.label: EventReservation
EventReservation.comment:
A reservation for an event like a concert, sporting event, or lecture.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use Offer.

EventScheduled.label: EventScheduled
EventScheduled.comment: The event is taking place or has taken place on the startDate as scheduled. Use of this value is optional, as it is assumed by default.

EventStatusType.label: EventStatusType
EventStatusType.comment: EventStatusType is an enumeration type whose instances represent several states that an Event may be in.

ExerciseAction.label: ExerciseAction
ExerciseAction.comment: The act of participating in exertive activity for the purposes of improving health and fitness.

ExhibitionEvent.label: ExhibitionEvent
ExhibitionEvent.comment: Event type: Exhibition event, e.g. at a museum, library, archive, tradeshow, ...

FAQPage.label: FAQPage
FAQPage.comment: A FAQPage is a WebPage presenting one or more "Frequently asked questions" (see also QAPage).

FMRadioChannel.label: FMRadioChannel
FMRadioChannel.comment: A radio channel that uses FM.

FailedActionStatus.label: FailedActionStatus
FailedActionStatus.comment: An action that failed to complete. The action's error property and the HTTP return code contain more information about the failure.

FilmAction.label: FilmAction
FilmAction.comment: The act of capturing sound and moving images on film, video, or digitally.

FinancialProduct.label: FinancialProduct
FinancialProduct.comment: A product provided to consumers and businesses by financial institutions such as banks, insurance companies, brokerage firms, consumer finance companies, and investment companies which comprise the financial services industry.

FindAction.label: FindAction
FindAction.comment:
The act of finding an object.



Related actions:



  • SearchAction: FindAction is generally lead by a SearchAction, but not necessarily.

FlightReservation.label: FlightReservation
FlightReservation.comment:
A reservation for air travel.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, use Offer.

FollowAction.label: FollowAction
FollowAction.comment:
The act of forming a personal connection with someone/something (object) unidirectionally/asymmetrically to get updates polled from.



Related actions:



  • BefriendAction: Unlike BefriendAction, FollowAction implies that the connection is not necessarily reciprocal.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, FollowAction implies that the follower acts as an active agent constantly/actively polling for updates.
  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in continuing receiving updates from the object.
  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, FollowAction implies that the agent is interested in getting updates from the object.
  • TrackAction: Unlike TrackAction, FollowAction refers to the polling of updates of all aspects of animate objects rather than the location of inanimate objects (e.g. you track a package, but you don't follow it).

FoodEstablishmentReservation.label: FoodEstablishmentReservation
FoodEstablishmentReservation.comment:
A reservation to dine at a food-related business.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

FoodService.label: FoodService
FoodService.comment: A food service, like breakfast, lunch, or dinner.

FourWheelDriveConfiguration.label: FourWheelDriveConfiguration
FourWheelDriveConfiguration.comment: Four-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine primarily drives two wheels with a part-time four-wheel drive capability.

Friday.label: Friday
Friday.comment: The day of the week between Thursday and Saturday.

FrontWheelDriveConfiguration.label: FrontWheelDriveConfiguration
FrontWheelDriveConfiguration.comment: Front-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives the front wheels.

Game.label: Game
Game.comment: The Game type represents things which are games. These are typically rule-governed recreational activities, e.g. role-playing games in which players assume the role of characters in a fictional setting.

GamePlayMode.label: GamePlayMode
GamePlayMode.comment: Indicates whether this game is multi-player, co-op or single-player.

GameServer.label: GameServer
GameServer.comment: Server that provides game interaction in a multiplayer game.

GeoCircle.label: GeoCircle
GeoCircle.comment: A GeoCircle is a GeoShape representing a circular geographic area. As it is a GeoShape          it provides the simple textual property 'circle', but also allows the combination of postalCode alongside geoRadius.          The center of the circle can be indicated via the 'geoMidpoint' property, or more approximately using 'address', 'postalCode'.

GeoCoordinates.label: GeoCoordinates
GeoCoordinates.comment: The geographic coordinates of a place or event.

GeoShape.label: GeoShape
GeoShape.comment: The geographic shape of a place. A GeoShape can be described using several properties whose values are based on latitude/longitude pairs. Either whitespace or commas can be used to separate latitude and longitude; whitespace should be used when writing a list of several such points.

GiveAction.label: GiveAction
GiveAction.comment:
The act of transferring ownership of an object to a destination. Reciprocal of TakeAction.



Related actions:



  • TakeAction: Reciprocal of GiveAction.
  • SendAction: Unlike SendAction, GiveAction implies that ownership is being transferred (e.g. I may send my laptop to you, but that doesn't mean I'm giving it to you).

GovernmentOffice.label: GovernmentOffice
GovernmentOffice.comment: A government office—for example, an IRS or DMV office.

GovernmentPermit.label: GovernmentPermit
GovernmentPermit.comment: A permit issued by a government agency.

GovernmentService.label: GovernmentService
GovernmentService.comment: A service provided by a government organization, e.g. food stamps, veterans benefits, etc.

GroupBoardingPolicy.label: GroupBoardingPolicy
GroupBoardingPolicy.comment: The airline boards by groups based on check-in time, priority, etc.

HVACBusiness.label: HVACBusiness
HVACBusiness.comment: A business that provide Heating, Ventilation and Air Conditioning services.

HalalDiet.label: HalalDiet
HalalDiet.comment: A diet conforming to Islamic dietary practices.

HearingImpairedSupported.label: HearingImpairedSupported
HearingImpairedSupported.comment: Uses devices to support users with hearing impairments.

HinduDiet.label: HinduDiet
HinduDiet.comment: A diet conforming to Hindu dietary practices, in particular, beef-free.

HobbyShop.label: HobbyShop
HobbyShop.comment: A store that sells materials useful or necessary for various hobbies.

HomeAndConstructionBusiness.label: HomeAndConstructionBusiness
HomeAndConstructionBusiness.comment:
A construction business.



A HomeAndConstructionBusiness is a LocalBusiness that provides services around homes and buildings.



As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).

Hostel.label: Hostel
Hostel.comment:
A hostel - cheap accommodation, often in shared dormitories.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Hotel.label: Hotel
Hotel.comment:
A hotel is an establishment that provides lodging paid on a short-term basis (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

HotelRoom.label: HotelRoom
HotelRoom.comment:
A hotel room is a single room in a hotel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

House.label: House
House.comment: A house is a building or structure that has the ability to be occupied for habitation by humans or other creatures (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House).

HowTo.label: HowTo
HowTo.comment: Instructions that explain how to achieve a result by performing a sequence of steps.

HowToDirection.label: HowToDirection
HowToDirection.comment: A direction indicating a single action to do in the instructions for how to achieve a result.

HowToItem.label: HowToItem
HowToItem.comment: An item used as either a tool or supply when performing the instructions for how to to achieve a result.

HowToSection.label: HowToSection
HowToSection.comment: A sub-grouping of steps in the instructions for how to achieve a result (e.g. steps for making a pie crust within a pie recipe).

HowToStep.label: HowToStep
HowToStep.comment: A step in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It is an ordered list with HowToDirection and/or HowToTip items.

HowToSupply.label: HowToSupply
HowToSupply.comment: A supply consumed when performing the instructions for how to achieve a result.

HowToTip.label: HowToTip
HowToTip.comment: An explanation in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It provides supplementary information about a technique, supply, author's preference, etc. It can explain what could be done, or what should not be done, but doesn't specify what should be done (see HowToDirection).

HowToTool.label: HowToTool
HowToTool.comment: A tool used (but not consumed) when performing instructions for how to achieve a result.

IgnoreAction.label: IgnoreAction
IgnoreAction.comment: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.

ImageGallery.label: ImageGallery
ImageGallery.comment: Web page type: Image gallery page.

InStock.label: InStock
InStock.comment: Indicates that the item is in stock.

InStoreOnly.label: InStoreOnly
InStoreOnly.comment: Indicates that the item is available only at physical locations.

IndividualProduct.label: IndividualProduct
IndividualProduct.comment: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).

InformAction.label: InformAction
InformAction.comment: The act of notifying someone of information pertinent to them, with no expectation of a response.

InsertAction.label: InsertAction
InsertAction.comment: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.

InstallAction.label: InstallAction
InstallAction.comment: The act of installing an application.

Intangible.label: Intangible
Intangible.comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.

InteractAction.label: InteractAction
InteractAction.comment: The act of interacting with another person or organization.

InteractionCounter.label: InteractionCounter
InteractionCounter.comment: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.

InvestmentOrDeposit.label: InvestmentOrDeposit
InvestmentOrDeposit.comment: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.

InviteAction.label: InviteAction
InviteAction.comment: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.

Invoice.label: Invoice
Invoice.comment: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.

ItemAvailability.label: ItemAvailability
ItemAvailability.comment: A list of possible product availability options.

ItemList.label: ItemList
ItemList.comment: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.

ItemListOrderAscending.label: ItemListOrderAscending
ItemListOrderAscending.comment: An ItemList ordered with lower values listed first.

ItemListOrderDescending.label: ItemListOrderDescending
ItemListOrderDescending.comment: An ItemList ordered with higher values listed first.

ItemListOrderType.label: ItemListOrderType
ItemListOrderType.comment: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.

ItemListUnordered.label: ItemListUnordered
ItemListUnordered.comment: An ItemList ordered with no explicit order.

ItemPage.label: ItemPage
ItemPage.comment: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.

JobPosting.label: JobPosting
JobPosting.comment: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.

JoinAction.label: JoinAction
JoinAction.comment:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.



Related actions:



  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.

KosherDiet.label: KosherDiet
KosherDiet.comment: A diet conforming to Jewish dietary practices.

Landform.label: Landform
Landform.comment: A landform or physical feature.  Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.

Language.label: Language
Language.comment: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in BCP 47 can be used via the alternateName property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using ComputerLanguage.

LeaveAction.label: LeaveAction
LeaveAction.comment:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.



Related actions:



  • JoinAction: The antonym of LeaveAction.
  • UnRegisterAction: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.

LeftHandDriving.label: LeftHandDriving
LeftHandDriving.comment: The steering position is on the left side of the vehicle (viewed from the main direction of driving).

LegalService.label: LegalService
LegalService.comment:
A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.



As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).

LegislativeBuilding.label: LegislativeBuilding
LegislativeBuilding.comment: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.

LendAction.label: LendAction
LendAction.comment:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.



Related actions:



  • BorrowAction: Reciprocal of LendAction.

LikeAction.label: LikeAction
LikeAction.comment: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.

LimitedAvailability.label: LimitedAvailability
LimitedAvailability.comment: Indicates that the item has limited availability.

LiquorStore.label: LiquorStore
LiquorStore.comment: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.

ListItem.label: ListItem
ListItem.comment: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.

ListenAction.label: ListenAction
ListenAction.comment: The act of consuming audio content.

LiveBlogPosting.label: LiveBlogPosting
LiveBlogPosting.comment: A blog post intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.

LoanOrCredit.label: LoanOrCredit
LoanOrCredit.comment: A financial product for the loaning of an amount of money under agreed terms and charges.

LocalBusiness.label: LocalBusiness
LocalBusiness.comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.

LocationFeatureSpecification.label: LocationFeatureSpecification
LocationFeatureSpecification.comment: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.

LockerDelivery.label: LockerDelivery
LockerDelivery.comment: A DeliveryMethod in which an item is made available via locker.

LodgingBusiness.label: LodgingBusiness
LodgingBusiness.comment: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.

LodgingReservation.label: LodgingReservation
LodgingReservation.comment:
A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

LoseAction.label: LoseAction
LoseAction.comment: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.

LowCalorieDiet.label: LowCalorieDiet
LowCalorieDiet.comment: A diet focused on reduced calorie intake.

LowFatDiet.label: LowFatDiet
LowFatDiet.comment: A diet focused on reduced fat and cholesterol intake.

LowLactoseDiet.label: LowLactoseDiet
LowLactoseDiet.comment: A diet appropriate for people with lactose intolerance.

LowSaltDiet.label: LowSaltDiet
LowSaltDiet.comment: A diet focused on reduced sodium intake.

MapCategoryType.label: MapCategoryType
MapCategoryType.comment: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.

MarryAction.label: MarryAction
MarryAction.comment: The act of marrying a person.

Mass.label: Mass
Mass.comment: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.

MediaGallery.label: MediaGallery
MediaGallery.comment: Web page type: Media gallery page. A mixed-media page that can contains media such as images, videos, and other multimedia.

MediaObject.label: MediaObject
MediaObject.comment: A media object, such as an image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).

MediaSubscription.label: MediaSubscription
MediaSubscription.comment: A subscription which allows a user to access media including audio, video, books, etc.

MedicalOrganization.label: MedicalOrganization
MedicalOrganization.comment: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.

MeetingRoom.label: MeetingRoom
MeetingRoom.comment:
A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Menu.label: Menu
Menu.comment: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.

MenuItem.label: MenuItem
MenuItem.comment: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.

MenuSection.label: MenuSection
MenuSection.comment: A sub-grouping of food or drink items in a menu. E.g. courses (such as 'Dinner', 'Breakfast', etc.), specific type of dishes (such as 'Meat', 'Vegan', 'Drinks', etc.), or some other classification made by the menu provider.

Message.label: Message
Message.comment: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.

MiddleSchool.label: MiddleSchool
MiddleSchool.comment: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).

MobileApplication.label: MobileApplication
MobileApplication.comment: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.

MobilePhoneStore.label: MobilePhoneStore
MobilePhoneStore.comment: A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.

Monday.label: Monday
Monday.comment: The day of the week between Sunday and Tuesday.

MonetaryAmount.label: MonetaryAmount
MonetaryAmount.comment: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use PriceSpecification Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.

MonetaryAmountDistribution.label: MonetaryAmountDistribution
MonetaryAmountDistribution.comment: A statistical distribution of monetary amounts.

Motel.label: Motel
Motel.comment:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

Mountain.label: Mountain
Mountain.comment: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.

MoveAction.label: MoveAction
MoveAction.comment:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.



Related actions:



  • TransferAction: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.

MovieClip.label: MovieClip
MovieClip.comment: A short segment/part of a movie.

MovieSeries.label: MovieSeries
MovieSeries.comment: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.

MultiPlayer.label: MultiPlayer
MultiPlayer.comment: Play mode: MultiPlayer. Requiring or allowing multiple human players to play simultaneously.

MusicAlbumProductionType.label: MusicAlbumProductionType
MusicAlbumProductionType.comment: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.

MusicAlbumReleaseType.label: MusicAlbumReleaseType
MusicAlbumReleaseType.comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.

MusicGroup.label: MusicGroup
MusicGroup.comment: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.

MusicPlaylist.label: MusicPlaylist
MusicPlaylist.comment: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.

MusicRecording.label: MusicRecording
MusicRecording.comment: A music recording (track), usually a single song.

MusicRelease.label: MusicRelease
MusicRelease.comment: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.

MusicReleaseFormatType.label: MusicReleaseFormatType
MusicReleaseFormatType.comment: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).

NewCondition.label: NewCondition
NewCondition.comment: Indicates that the item is new.

NewsArticle.label: NewsArticle
NewsArticle.comment:
A NewsArticle is an article whose content reports news, or provides background context and supporting materials for understanding the news.



A more detailed overview of schema.org News markup is also available.

NoteDigitalDocument.label: NoteDigitalDocument
NoteDigitalDocument.comment: A file containing a note, primarily for the author.

Number.label: Number
Number.comment:
Data type: Number.



Usage guidelines:



  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.

Occupation.label: Occupation
Occupation.comment: A profession, may involve prolonged training and/or a formal qualification.

Offer.label: Offer
Offer.comment:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.



Note: As the businessFunction property, which identifies the form of offer (e.g. sell, lease, repair, dispose), defaults to http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Sell; an Offer without a defined businessFunction value can be assumed to be an offer to sell.



For GTIN-related fields, see Check Digit calculator and validation guide from GS1.

OfferCatalog.label: OfferCatalog
OfferCatalog.comment: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.

OfferItemCondition.label: OfferItemCondition
OfferItemCondition.comment: A list of possible conditions for the item.

OfflinePermanently.label: OfflinePermanently
OfflinePermanently.comment: Game server status: OfflinePermanently. Server is offline and not available.

OfflineTemporarily.label: OfflineTemporarily
OfflineTemporarily.comment: Game server status: OfflineTemporarily. Server is offline now but it can be online soon.

OnDemandEvent.label: OnDemandEvent
OnDemandEvent.comment: A publication event e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.

OnSitePickup.label: OnSitePickup
OnSitePickup.comment: A DeliveryMethod in which an item is collected on site, e.g. in a store or at a box office.

Online.label: Online
Online.comment: Game server status: Online. Server is available.

OnlineFull.label: OnlineFull
OnlineFull.comment: Game server status: OnlineFull. Server is online but unavailable. The maximum number of players has reached.

OnlineOnly.label: OnlineOnly
OnlineOnly.comment: Indicates that the item is available only online.

OpeningHoursSpecification.label: OpeningHoursSpecification
OpeningHoursSpecification.comment:
A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.



The place is open if the opens property is specified, and closed otherwise.



If the value for the closes property is less than the value for the opens property then the hour range is assumed to span over the next day.

Order.label: Order
Order.comment: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.

OrderAction.label: OrderAction
OrderAction.comment: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

OrderCancelled.label: OrderCancelled
OrderCancelled.comment: OrderStatus representing cancellation of an order.

OrderDelivered.label: OrderDelivered
OrderDelivered.comment: OrderStatus representing successful delivery of an order.

OrderInTransit.label: OrderInTransit
OrderInTransit.comment: OrderStatus representing that an order is in transit.

OrderItem.label: OrderItem
OrderItem.comment: An order item is a line of an order. It includes the quantity and shipping details of a bought offer.

OrderPaymentDue.label: OrderPaymentDue
OrderPaymentDue.comment: OrderStatus representing that payment is due on an order.

OrderPickupAvailable.label: OrderPickupAvailable
OrderPickupAvailable.comment: OrderStatus representing availability of an order for pickup.

OrderProblem.label: OrderProblem
OrderProblem.comment: OrderStatus representing that there is a problem with the order.

OrderProcessing.label: OrderProcessing
OrderProcessing.comment: OrderStatus representing that an order is being processed.

OrderReturned.label: OrderReturned
OrderReturned.comment: OrderStatus representing that an order has been returned.

Organization.label: Organization
Organization.comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.

OrganizationRole.label: OrganizationRole
OrganizationRole.comment: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.

OrganizeAction.label: OrganizeAction
OrganizeAction.comment: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.

OutOfStock.label: OutOfStock
OutOfStock.comment: Indicates that the item is out of stock.

OwnershipInfo.label: OwnershipInfo
OwnershipInfo.comment: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.

PaintAction.label: PaintAction
PaintAction.comment: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.

ParcelDelivery.label: ParcelDelivery
ParcelDelivery.comment: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.

ParcelService.label: ParcelService
ParcelService.comment:
A private parcel service as the delivery mode available for a certain offer.



Commonly used values:



  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS

ParentAudience.label: ParentAudience
ParentAudience.comment: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.

ParkingFacility.label: ParkingFacility
ParkingFacility.comment: A parking lot or other parking facility.

PawnShop.label: PawnShop
PawnShop.comment: A shop that will buy, or lend money against the security of, personal possessions.

PayAction.label: PayAction
PayAction.comment: An agent pays a price to a participant.

PaymentAutomaticallyApplied.label: PaymentAutomaticallyApplied
PaymentAutomaticallyApplied.comment: An automatic payment system is in place and will be used.

PaymentCard.label: PaymentCard
PaymentCard.comment: A payment method using a credit, debit, store or other card to associate the payment with an account.

PaymentChargeSpecification.label: PaymentChargeSpecification
PaymentChargeSpecification.comment: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.

PaymentComplete.label: PaymentComplete
PaymentComplete.comment: The payment has been received and processed.

PaymentDeclined.label: PaymentDeclined
PaymentDeclined.comment: The payee received the payment, but it was declined for some reason.

PaymentDue.label: PaymentDue
PaymentDue.comment: The payment is due, but still within an acceptable time to be received.

PaymentMethod.label: PaymentMethod
PaymentMethod.comment:
A payment method is a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase. Payment methods are characterized by the legal and technical structures used, and by the organization or group carrying out the transaction.



Commonly used values:



  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByInvoice
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Cash
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#CheckInAdvance
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#COD
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DirectDebit
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#GoogleCheckout
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PayPal
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PaySwarm

PaymentPastDue.label: PaymentPastDue
PaymentPastDue.comment: The payment is due and considered late.

PaymentService.label: PaymentService
PaymentService.comment: A Service to transfer funds from a person or organization to a beneficiary person or organization.

PaymentStatusType.label: PaymentStatusType
PaymentStatusType.comment: A specific payment status. For example, PaymentDue, PaymentComplete, etc.

PeopleAudience.label: PeopleAudience
PeopleAudience.comment: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.

PerformAction.label: PerformAction
PerformAction.comment: The act of participating in performance arts.

PerformanceRole.label: PerformanceRole
PerformanceRole.comment: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.

PerformingArtsTheater.label: PerformingArtsTheater
PerformingArtsTheater.comment: A theater or other performing art center.

PerformingGroup.label: PerformingGroup
PerformingGroup.comment: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.

Periodical.label: Periodical
Periodical.comment:
A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper to continue indefinitely.



See also blog post.

Permit.label: Permit
Permit.comment: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.

Person.label: Person
Person.comment: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

PhotographAction.label: PhotographAction
PhotographAction.comment: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.

Place.label: Place
Place.comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.

PlaceOfWorship.label: PlaceOfWorship
PlaceOfWorship.comment: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.

PlanAction.label: PlanAction
PlanAction.comment: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.

PlayAction.label: PlayAction
PlayAction.comment:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, Competition or exercise.



Related actions:



  • ListenAction: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
  • WatchAction: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.

PotentialActionStatus.label: PotentialActionStatus
PotentialActionStatus.comment: A description of an action that is supported.

PreOrder.label: PreOrder
PreOrder.comment: Indicates that the item is available for pre-order.

PreOrderAction.label: PreOrderAction
PreOrderAction.comment: An agent orders a (not yet released) object/product/service to be delivered/sent.

PreSale.label: PreSale
PreSale.comment: Indicates that the item is available for ordering and delivery before general availability.

PrependAction.label: PrependAction
PrependAction.comment: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.

PresentationDigitalDocument.label: PresentationDigitalDocument
PresentationDigitalDocument.comment: A file containing slides or used for a presentation.

PriceSpecification.label: PriceSpecification
PriceSpecification.comment: A structured value representing a price or price range. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup. It is recommended to use MonetaryAmount to describe independent amounts of money such as a salary, credit card limits, etc.

Product.label: Product
Product.comment: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.

ProductModel.label: ProductModel
ProductModel.comment: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).

ProfessionalService.label: ProfessionalService
ProfessionalService.comment:
Original definition: "provider of professional services."



The general ProfessionalService type for local businesses was deprecated due to confusion with Service. For reference, the types that it included were: Dentist, AccountingService, Attorney, Notary, as well as types for several kinds of HomeAndConstructionBusiness: Electrician, GeneralContractor, HousePainter, Locksmith, Plumber, RoofingContractor. LegalService was introduced as a more inclusive supertype of Attorney.

ProgramMembership.label: ProgramMembership
ProgramMembership.comment: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.

PropertyValue.label: PropertyValue
PropertyValue.comment:
A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.



Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.

PublicHolidays.label: PublicHolidays
PublicHolidays.comment: This stands for any day that is a public holiday; it is a placeholder for all official public holidays in some particular location. While not technically a "day of the week", it can be used with OpeningHoursSpecification. In the context of an opening hours specification it can be used to indicate opening hours on public holidays, overriding general opening hours for the day of the week on which a public holiday occurs.

PublicationEvent.label: PublicationEvent
PublicationEvent.comment: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.

PublicationIssue.label: PublicationIssue
PublicationIssue.comment:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.



See also blog post.

PublicationVolume.label: PublicationVolume
PublicationVolume.comment:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.



See also blog post.

QAPage.label: QAPage
QAPage.comment: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).

QualitativeValue.label: QualitativeValue
QualitativeValue.comment: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.

QuantitativeValue.label: QuantitativeValue
QuantitativeValue.comment: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.

Quantity.label: Quantity
Quantity.comment: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 Kg' or '4 milligrams'.

Question.label: Question
Question.comment: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.

QuoteAction.label: QuoteAction
QuoteAction.comment: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.

RVPark.label: RVPark
RVPark.comment: A place offering space for "Recreational Vehicles", Caravans, mobile homes and the like.

RadioChannel.label: RadioChannel
RadioChannel.comment: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.

RadioClip.label: RadioClip
RadioClip.comment: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.

RadioEpisode.label: RadioEpisode
RadioEpisode.comment: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.

RadioSeason.label: RadioSeason
RadioSeason.comment: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

RadioSeries.label: RadioSeries
RadioSeries.comment: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.

Rating.label: Rating
Rating.comment: A rating is an evaluation on a numeric scale, such as 1 to 5 stars.

ReactAction.label: ReactAction
ReactAction.comment: The act of responding instinctively and emotionally to an object, expressing a sentiment.

ReadAction.label: ReadAction
ReadAction.comment: The act of consuming written content.

ReadPermission.label: ReadPermission
ReadPermission.comment: Permission to read or view the document.

RearWheelDriveConfiguration.label: RearWheelDriveConfiguration
RearWheelDriveConfiguration.comment: Real-wheel drive is a transmission layout where the engine drives the rear wheels.

ReceiveAction.label: ReceiveAction
ReceiveAction.comment:
The act of physically/electronically taking delivery of an object thathas been transferred from an origin to a destination. Reciprocal of SendAction.



Related actions:



  • SendAction: The reciprocal of ReceiveAction.
  • TakeAction: Unlike TakeAction, ReceiveAction does not imply that the ownership has been transfered (e.g. I can receive a package, but it does not mean the package is now mine).

Recipe.label: Recipe
Recipe.comment: A recipe. For dietary restrictions covered by the recipe, a few common restrictions are enumerated via suitableForDiet. The keywords property can also be used to add more detail.

RefurbishedCondition.label: RefurbishedCondition
RefurbishedCondition.comment: Indicates that the item is refurbished.

RegisterAction.label: RegisterAction
RegisterAction.comment:
The act of registering to be a user of a service, product or web page.



Related actions:



  • JoinAction: Unlike JoinAction, RegisterAction implies you are registering to be a user of a service, not a group/team of people.
  • [FollowAction]]: Unlike FollowAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting to poll for updates from the object.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, RegisterAction doesn't imply that the agent is expecting updates from the object.

RejectAction.label: RejectAction
RejectAction.comment:
The act of rejecting to/adopting an object.



Related actions:



  • AcceptAction: The antonym of RejectAction.

RentAction.label: RentAction
RentAction.comment: The act of giving money in return for temporary use, but not ownership, of an object such as a vehicle or property. For example, an agent rents a property from a landlord in exchange for a periodic payment.

RentalCarReservation.label: RentalCarReservation
RentalCarReservation.comment:
A reservation for a rental car.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.

ReplaceAction.label: ReplaceAction
ReplaceAction.comment: The act of editing a recipient by replacing an old object with a new object.

ReplyAction.label: ReplyAction
ReplyAction.comment:
The act of responding to a question/message asked/sent by the object. Related to AskAction



Related actions:



  • AskAction: Appears generally as an origin of a ReplyAction.

Report.label: Report
Report.comment: A Report generated by governmental or non-governmental organization.

Reservation.label: Reservation
Reservation.comment:
Describes a reservation for travel, dining or an event. Some reservations require tickets.



Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations. For offers of tickets, restaurant reservations, flights, or rental cars, use Offer.

ReservationCancelled.label: ReservationCancelled
ReservationCancelled.comment: The status for a previously confirmed reservation that is now cancelled.

ReservationConfirmed.label: ReservationConfirmed
ReservationConfirmed.comment: The status of a confirmed reservation.

ReservationHold.label: ReservationHold
ReservationHold.comment: The status of a reservation on hold pending an update like credit card number or flight changes.

ReservationPackage.label: ReservationPackage
ReservationPackage.comment: A group of multiple reservations with common values for all sub-reservations.

ReservationPending.label: ReservationPending
ReservationPending.comment: The status of a reservation when a request has been sent, but not confirmed.

ReserveAction.label: ReserveAction
ReserveAction.comment:
Reserving a concrete object.



Related actions:



  • ScheduleAction: Unlike ScheduleAction, ReserveAction reserves concrete objects (e.g. a table, a hotel) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

Reservoir.label: Reservoir
Reservoir.comment: A reservoir of water, typically an artificially created lake, like the Lake Kariba reservoir.

Residence.label: Residence
Residence.comment: The place where a person lives.

Resort.label: Resort
Resort.comment:
A resort is a place used for relaxation or recreation, attracting visitors for holidays or vacations. Resorts are places, towns or sometimes commercial establishment operated by a single company (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

RestrictedDiet.label: RestrictedDiet
RestrictedDiet.comment: A diet restricted to certain foods or preparations for cultural, religious, health or lifestyle reasons.

ResumeAction.label: ResumeAction
ResumeAction.comment: The act of resuming a device or application which was formerly paused (e.g. resume music playback or resume a timer).

ReturnAction.label: ReturnAction
ReturnAction.comment: The act of returning to the origin that which was previously received (concrete objects) or taken (ownership).

Review.label: Review
Review.comment: A review of an item - for example, of a restaurant, movie, or store.

ReviewAction.label: ReviewAction
ReviewAction.comment: The act of producing a balanced opinion about the object for an audience. An agent reviews an object with participants resulting in a review.

RightHandDriving.label: RightHandDriving
RightHandDriving.comment: The steering position is on the right side of the vehicle (viewed from the main direction of driving).

RiverBodyOfWater.label: RiverBodyOfWater
RiverBodyOfWater.comment: A river (for example, the broad majestic Shannon).

Role.label: Role
Role.comment:
Represents additional information about a relationship or property. For example a Role can be used to say that a 'member' role linking some SportsTeam to a player occurred during a particular time period. Or that a Person's 'actor' role in a Movie was for some particular characterName. Such properties can be attached to a Role entity, which is then associated with the main entities using ordinary properties like 'member' or 'actor'.



See also blog post.

Room.label: Room
Room.comment:
A room is a distinguishable space within a structure, usually separated from other spaces by interior walls. (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.

RsvpAction.label: RsvpAction
RsvpAction.comment: The act of notifying an event organizer as to whether you expect to attend the event.

RsvpResponseMaybe.label: RsvpResponseMaybe
RsvpResponseMaybe.comment: The invitee may or may not attend.

RsvpResponseType.label: RsvpResponseType
RsvpResponseType.comment: RsvpResponseType is an enumeration type whose instances represent responding to an RSVP request.

Saturday.label: Saturday
Saturday.comment: The day of the week between Friday and Sunday.

ScheduleAction.label: ScheduleAction
ScheduleAction.comment:
Scheduling future actions, events, or tasks.



Related actions:



  • ReserveAction: Unlike ReserveAction, ScheduleAction allocates future actions (e.g. an event, a task, etc) towards a time slot / spatial allocation.

ScreeningEvent.label: ScreeningEvent
ScreeningEvent.comment: A screening of a movie or other video.

SeaBodyOfWater.label: SeaBodyOfWater
SeaBodyOfWater.comment: A sea (for example, the Caspian sea).

SearchAction.label: SearchAction
SearchAction.comment:
The act of searching for an object.



Related actions:



  • FindAction: SearchAction generally leads to a FindAction, but not necessarily.

SearchResultsPage.label: SearchResultsPage
SearchResultsPage.comment: Web page type: Search results page.

Season.label: Season
Season.comment: A media season e.g. tv, radio, video game etc.

Seat.label: Seat
Seat.comment: Used to describe a seat, such as a reserved seat in an event reservation.

SellAction.label: SellAction
SellAction.comment: The act of taking money from a buyer in exchange for goods or services rendered. An agent sells an object, product, or service to a buyer for a price. Reciprocal of BuyAction.

SendAction.label: SendAction
SendAction.comment:
The act of physically/electronically dispatching an object for transfer from an origin to a destination.Related actions:



  • ReceiveAction: The reciprocal of SendAction.
  • GiveAction: Unlike GiveAction, SendAction does not imply the transfer of ownership (e.g. I can send you my laptop, but I'm not necessarily giving it to you).

Series.label: Series
Series.comment: A Series in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. See also CreativeWorkSeries, EventSeries.

Service.label: Service
Service.comment: A service provided by an organization, e.g. delivery service, print services, etc.

ServiceChannel.label: ServiceChannel
ServiceChannel.comment: A means for accessing a service, e.g. a government office location, web site, or phone number.

ShareAction.label: ShareAction
ShareAction.comment: The act of distributing content to people for their amusement or edification.

SinglePlayer.label: SinglePlayer
SinglePlayer.comment: Play mode: SinglePlayer. Which is played by a lone player.

SiteNavigationElement.label: SiteNavigationElement
SiteNavigationElement.comment: A navigation element of the page.

SocialMediaPosting.label: SocialMediaPosting
SocialMediaPosting.comment: A post to a social media platform, including blog posts, tweets, Facebook posts, etc.

SoftwareSourceCode.label: SoftwareSourceCode
SoftwareSourceCode.comment: Computer programming source code. Example: Full (compile ready) solutions, code snippet samples, scripts, templates.

SoldOut.label: SoldOut
SoldOut.comment: Indicates that the item has sold out.

SomeProducts.label: SomeProducts
SomeProducts.comment: A placeholder for multiple similar products of the same kind.

SpeakableSpecification.label: SpeakableSpecification
